                    <p>“Follow me!” The deep voice commanded, its effect quite intimidating. I complied and followed him through the castle’s many tunnels that stank of dead rats and rotten food, the smell bringing forth a nauseating effect in my throat and stomach. After going through lots of turns through the tunnels, and succumbing to holding my breath and barf, I finally felt the cold night air on my skin, breathed it wholly. The air, so cold yet so sweet, spelt of only one word, freedom. I had finally attained it, and now I would be able to go back home, back to that place I hated so earlier, but now missed it so that I considered it heaven. </p>
<p>“Come here, quick!” The voice beckoned, and I realized I had been standing on a pathway, lost in my own thoughts. I followed him as he got onto a horse, and as the horse galloped away, a voice screeched from behind, “She is getting away!”</p>
<p>Shouts arose in the once silent castle as the guards cried out commands to each other, their horses neighing and galloping. I stole a glance at the charging guards and shrieked in horror, noting the huge warhorses galloping faster compared to our horse. Moreover, the guards, who were getting closer by every minute, had their bows and fiery arrows fixated on us, waiting for the command to shoot at us.</p>
<p>“There are going to kill us!” I shrieked, panic within me arising, as I noticed another group of the guards guarding the entrance that we neared, their bows and arrows fixated at us.</p>
					
